Neil Aggett was tortured in the week leading up to his death. This was the evidence given on Thursday by Jabu Ngwenya, a former political detainee, who testified at the inquest into his death. JOHANNESBURG - Former security branch officer, Paul Erasmus is expected to take the stand at the Neil Aggett inquiry on Tuesday. Aggett died in police custody in February 1982. On Monday, Witness Keith Coleman testified. Aggett inquest: Former security branch officer claims he was forced to lie Coleman had started a community newspaper reflecting the struggle of black South Africans during apartheid. This landed him on the police's wanted list and he was detained at the police station at the same time as Aggett.